{{Infobox named horse |horsename= Fadjur |image= |caption= |breed=[[Arabian horse|Arabian]] |discipline= |sire= Fadheilan |grandsire=[[Henry Babson|*Fadl]] |dam= Bint Sahara |damsire= Farawi |sex= Stallion |foaled= 1952 |country= United States |color= |breeder=Harry Linden |owner= Marge Tone |racerecord= |raceearnings= |racewins= |raceawards= |otherawards |honors= |updated= March 13, 2008 }}
'''Fadjur''', Foaled April 12, 1952, died 1983, was an [[Arabian horse]] who was bred in [[Spokane, Washington]] and resided in Stockton, [[California]]. A [[bay (horse)|bay]] [[stallion]], he was nicknamed "The Fabulous Fadjur" and sired numerous progeny from the Jack Tone Ranch over a thirty-year period.<ref name=Legends248>Carpenter ''Arabian Legends'' p. 248-259</ref>
He was a prolific breeder of champion horses,<ref name=Legends248/> and is the maternal grandsire of [[Khemosabi]].<ref name=Legends261>Carpenter ''Arabian Legends'' p. 261</ref>
