{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Use British English|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox football biography |name = George Adey |image = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = 1869 |birth_place = [[Handsworth, West Midlands|Handsworth]], England |death_date = |death_place = [[Birmingham]], England |height = |position = [[Wing half]] / [[Inside forward]] |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = – |clubs1 = Bournbrook |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = – |clubs2 = [[Stourbridge F.C.|Stourbridge]] |caps2 = |goals2 = |years3 = 1898–1902 |clubs3 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] |caps3 = 71 |goals3 = 1 |years4 = 1902–19?? |clubs4 = [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering]] |caps4 = |goals4 = |totalcaps = |totalgoals = }} '''George W. Adey''' (1869 – after 1901) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] born in [[Handsworth, West Midlands|Handsworth]], [[Birmingham]], who played as a [[wing half]] or [[inside forward]]. He made 71 appearances for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] in [[the Football League]], and went on to play for [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering]] of the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData (Tony Brown) |location=Nottingham |year=2004 |page=6 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Matthews |first=Tony |title=Birmingham City: A Complete Record |year=1995 |publisher=Breedon Books |location=Derby |page=68 |isbn=978-1-85983-010-9}}</ref>
In a 1901 profile of the Small Heath club and players in the ''[[Daily Express]]'', [[C.B. Fry]] wrote that "Adey is not showy, but he is a fine tackler, and remarkably persistent", and that he and his half-back colleagues [[Alex Leake]] and [[Walter Wigmore]] "get through an amount of work that is simply astonishing".<ref>{{cite news |last=Fry |first=C.B. |authorlink=C.B. Fry |title=Football Gossip. The Small Heath Club and its members. How they play |work=Daily Express |date=26 October 1901 |page=8}}</ref>
