{{hatnote|For other people named "Ludwig Lange", see [[Ludwig Lange (disambiguation)]]}} '''Ludwig Lange''' (born June 21, 1863 in [[Gießen]]; died July 12, 1936 in [[Weinsberg]]) was a [[Germans|German]] [[physicist]].
==Biography== He was the son of the philologist and archaeologist [[Ludwig Lange (philologist)|Ludwig Lange]] and his wife Adelheide Blume. He studied [[mathematics]], [[physics]], and also [[psychology]], [[epistemology]], [[ethics]] at the [[University of Leipzig]] and the [[University of Gießen]] from 1882-1885. He was an assistant of [[Wilhelm Wundt]] from 1885-1887 and attained his [[Ph.D.]] in 1886. He was working many years as a [[Privatdozent]], and in the field of [[photography]]. Since 1887 he exhibited growing symptoms of a [[Neuropathy|nervous disease]]. In 1936 he died in a [[psychiatric hospital]] ([[Klinikum am Weissenhof]]) in Weinsberg.<ref>Laue 1948, 1982</ref>
==Legacy== Lange is known for inventing terms like [[inertial frame of reference]] and inertial time (1885), which were used by him instead of Newton's "absolute space and time". This was very important for the development of [[Special relativity|relativistic mechanics]] after 1900. DiSalle describes Lange's definition in this way:<ref>DiSalle 2002</ref>
{{Cquote|An inertial system is a coordinate system with respect to which three free particles, projected from a single point and moving in non-coplanar directions, move in straight lines and travel mutually-proportional distances. The law of inertia then states that relative to any inertial system, any fourth free particle will move uniformly.}}
==Works== * {{Cite journal | author=Lange, L. | year=1885 | title=Über die wissenschaftliche Fassung des Galileischen Beharrungsgesetzes | journal=Philosophische Studien | pp=266–297 | volume=2}}
* {{Cite journal | author=Lange, L. | year=1885 | title=Über das Beharrungsgesetz. Berichte über Verhandlungen der Königlich Sächsischen Gesellschaft der Wissenschaften | journal=Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse | pp=333–351 | location=Leipzig | volume=}} * {{Cite book | author=Lange, L. | year=1886 | title=Die geschichtliche Entwicklung des Bewegungsbegriffs und ihr voraussichtliches Endergebnis | publisher= W. Engelmann | location=Leipzig}} * {{Cite journal | author=Lange, L. | year=1902 | title=Das Inertialsystem vor dem Forum der Naturforschung | journal=Philosophische Studien | pp=1–71 | volume=20}}
